# Odoo Jewelry Management System — Security Assessment Report

**Project:** odoo-jawlery (Odoo 17.0 Jewelry Management Suite)
**Assessment Type:** White-box source code review
**Date:** July 2025
**Framework:** OWASP Web Security Testing Guide (WSTG) / OWASP Top 10 (2021)

---

## Executive Summary

A white-box security assessment of the **Odoo Jewelry Management System** identified **six confirmed vulnerabilities** across the four custom addon modules (`jewelry_core`, `jewelry_transactions`, `jewelry_accounting`, `jewelry_dashboard`).

**Overall Risk Posture:** Elevated

| Severity | Count |
|----------|-------|
| High | 5 |
| Medium | 1 |
| Low | 0 |

All confirmed vulnerabilities have been remediated with code patches applied during the assessment.

---

## Methodology

**Assessment Type:** White-box source code review
**Framework:** OWASP Web Security Testing Guide (WSTG) and OWASP Top 10 (2021)
**Target:** `addons/` directory of the odoo-jawlery repository

**Activities performed:**

1. **Code Map & Architecture Understanding** — Full repository structure analysis, manifest review, dependency mapping, data flow tracing across the 4 addon modules.

2. **SAST Tooling** — Automated static analysis using Semgrep (Python/OWASP rules), Gitleaks (secret detection), Trufflehog (secret scanning), Trivy (dependency scanning), and AST-grep (structural code analysis).

3. **Manual Code Review** — Focused review of all model files, controllers, security ACLs, wizard logic, and external API integrations. Particular attention given to SSRF vectors (configurable API URLs), XSS (HTML rendering without encoding), access control (ACL entries and record rules), and business logic (payment flows, balance computations, gold credit handling).

4. **Validation** — Each finding was validated through comprehensive code-traced evidence, confirming both exploit path and root cause before filing.

5. **Remediation** — All confirmed vulnerabilities were fixed with targeted code patches, including input validation, output encoding, access control enforcement, and race condition mitigation.

