## Additional Findings

### Weak Default Password

The default admin password in `config/odoo.conf` is set to `admin`. This is a widely known default and should be changed immediately to a strong, randomly generated password.

### Public ACLs in jewelry_core

Nine ACL entries in `addons/jewelry_core/security/ir.model.access.csv` still use an empty `group_id` (effectively public within the organization):

| Model | Permission |
|-------|-----------|
| `metal.type` | Read-only |
| `gold.rate.history` | Read-only |
| `silver.rate.history` | Read-only |

While these are read-only, sensitive rate data is exposed to all internal users.

### Unrestricted Register Auto-Creation

`_find_or_create_register()` in `cash_register_line.py` auto-creates daily cash registers on first use without explicit authorization. The fix restricts this to today's date only.

